# Project Setup & Architecture — Tradly Boilerplate

## What This Boilerplate Is

A ready-to-use foundation for building Tradly-powered marketplace apps (product, event, service, donation).
Duplicate this repo for each new project — do not modify the boilerplate in place.

It handles: auth (sign-in/up/OTP/social/refresh/logout), listing (list/detail/like/unlike),
and cart (get/add/delete/clear) — with all caching, state sync, and SDK wiring already done.

---

## Package Installation

### Required — boilerplate core

```bash
npm install @reduxjs/toolkit react-redux redux-persist tradly
```

| Package | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `@reduxjs/toolkit` | Redux store + RTK Query (data fetching + caching) |
| `react-redux` | React bindings — `useSelector`, `useDispatch`, `Provider` |
| `redux-persist` | Persists `auth` + `app` slices to localStorage across reloads |
| `tradly` | Tradly JS SDK — all marketplace API calls go through this |

### Required — types only (devDependencies)

```bash
npm install -D typescript @types/react @types/react-dom
```

### Framework — choose one (not included)

```bash
# Next.js (recommended for marketplaces — SSR + routing built-in)
npx create-next-app@latest

# Vite + React (lighter, SPA-only)
npm create vite@latest -- --template react-ts
```

### Optional — commonly needed in marketplace UIs

```bash
# UUID for guest cart (already bundled in config/uuid.ts — no package needed)

# Form handling
npm install react-hook-form zod

# Toast notifications (used in flow examples)
npm install react-hot-toast
# OR
npm install sonner

# Routing (if not using Next.js)
npm install react-router-dom
```

