## Environment Setup

Create `.env` in your project root:

```env
VITE_TRADLY_DOMAIN=yourworkspace.tradly.co
VITE_TRADLY_PK_KEY=your_public_key_here
VITE_TRADLY_ENV=production
VITE_DEFAULT_CURRENCY=USD
VITE_DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=en
```

For Next.js rename vars to `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` and update `config/app.config.ts`:

```ts
// config/app.config.ts — Next.js version
domain: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_TRADLY_DOMAIN ?? '',
pkKey:  process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_TRADLY_PK_KEY  ?? '',
```

