## Cache Invalidation Map — Full Picture

This is what happens automatically — no manual `setState` ever needed.

| Action | Cart cache | Listing cache (`liked` / `in_cart`) |
|---|---|---|
| `signIn` / `verifyOtp` / `socialSignIn` | invalidate → re-fetch with auth | invalidate → re-fetch with auth |
| `addToCart` | invalidate | invalidate (`in_cart → true`) |
| `deleteCartItem` | invalidate | invalidate (`in_cart → false`) |
| `clearCart` | invalidate | invalidate (`in_cart → false` on all) |
| `likeListing` / `unlikeListing` | — | invalidate (`liked` toggles) |
| `logout` | **full reset** | **full reset** |
| `refreshAuth` fail | **full reset** | **full reset** |

**invalidate** = RTK Query marks the tag stale → re-fetches while any subscriber is mounted
**full reset** = entire API cache wiped → next mount starts from scratch (guest state)

